==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Priority
<hw>Pri*or"i*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>priorit⟦eacute⟧</ets>. See <er>Prior</er>, <pos>a.</pos>]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>The quality or state of being prior or antecedent in
time, or of preceding something else; <as>as, <ex>priority</ex> of
application</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Precedence; superior rank.</def>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Priority of debts</b></col>, <cd>a superior claim to
payment, or a claim to payment before others.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Antecedence; precedence;
pre⟦eum⟧minence.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Priorly</ent>⟦br⟧
